Subject: [PATCH] serial: ioc4: remove tty_port.low_latency assignment

tty_port.low_latency was removed in v5.12 (commit b3b576461c47).
All tty ports are now low latency by default, so the assignment
is both unnecessary and a build error.

--- a/drivers/tty/serial/ioc4_serial.c	2026-03-10 02:59:46.000000000 +0000
+++ b/drivers/tty/serial/ioc4_serial.c	2026-03-10 03:10:27.121442019 +0000
@@ -1743,8 +1743,6 @@
 
 	the_port->ignore_status_mask = N_ALL_INPUT;
 
-	state->port.low_latency = 1;
-
 	if (iflag & IGNPAR)
 		the_port->ignore_status_mask &= ~(N_PARITY_ERROR
 						| N_FRAMING_ERROR);
